<TITLE> 45th DU Convocation 'largest ever' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 12 (bdnews24.com)  The 45th convocation of Dhaka University, the largest in its history, took off Saturday with 9,000 graduates and post graduates receiving their degrees in high spirits. President Zillur Rahman, chancellor of Dhaka University, inaugurated the main convocation programme at midday, at the university's central sports ground, after playing of the national anthem. The university conferred honorary degrees to three noted academics  Nobel prize-winning chemist Prof Yuan T Lee, inventor of the Sono arsenic filter Abul Hussam and Indian historian Prof Ranajit Guha. Lee received his honorary degree in person. Hussam, a former DU student, and Guha were not present at the ceremony. Among the students receiving certificates 4,203 were graduates, 1,328 post graduates and 58 MPhil holders and 58 PhD holders. The university has said this is the largest convocation in terms of number of graduates and guests. Dhaka University was established in 1921. Its first convocation was held in 1923. Four convocations have been held since Bangladesh's independence in 1999, 2000, 2004 and the current one of 2009. bdn
